{{Infobox dam | name = Shah wa Arus Dam | image = | image_caption =Shah wa Arus Dam | name_official = | dam_crosses = [[Shakardara River]] | res_name = | location = [[Kabul Province]], [[Afghanistan]] | operator =[[Government of Afghanistan|Afghanistan]] | dam_length = | dam_height = {{Convert|75|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | dam_width_base = {{Convert|60|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | construction_began =2012 | opening =2016 | cost = $41 million | res_capacity_total = {{Convert|180000|m3|acre.ft|0|abbr=on}} | dam_type = gravity | res_catchment = | res_surface = | plant_capacity =1.2MW | plant_commission =2016 | plant_turbines = 2 x 600 [[kilowatt|KW]] | location_map =Afghanistan | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|34.688028|N|69.019386|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | extra = }}
The '''Shah wa Arus Dam''' is a 75m high concrete gravity dam under construction on the Shakardara River, located 22&nbsp;km away from [[Kabul City]], [[Afghanistan]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.parhoon-tarh.com/newsdetail-25-en.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-08-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130201043130/http://www.parhoon-tarh.com/newsdetail-25-en.html |archivedate=2013-02-01 |df= }}</ref> The dam with a 60m wide three-bay spillway is mainly geared towards provision of irrigation water as well as flood control and reliable year-round water supply to the city of Kabul as well as the district of [[Shakardara]]. The bidding process deadline was on 24 March 2014 to build the Shah-wa-Arus irrigation and hydropower project, which includes a rockfill dam, intake, powerhouse, pickup weir with balancing reservoir and head regulators, and right and left side main canals.<ref>http://www.tablieh.com/</ref> Tablieh and Parhoon Tarh JV Company was chosen as the main contractor for the project in a Design-Build contract in which the design services are provided by Alborz Sazeh Company.<ref>http://www.bakhtarnews.com.af/eng/business/item/2766-president-karzai-opens-shah-arus-power-dam/2766-president-karzai-opens-shah-arus-power-dam.html?start=20</ref>
President Ghani accompanied by ministers of water and energy and economy minister, national Security Council advisor , Kabul Governor and members of the National Assembly opened the construction work on the dam on 19 June 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://parhoon-tarh.sampa.ir/newsdetail-18-en.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-08-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130218145412/http://parhoon-tarh.sampa.ir/newsdetail-18-en.html |archivedate=2013-02-18 |df= }}</ref> The Dam will cost $41 million, with 81 meters height at the rocky base and about 330 000 cubic meters of concrete, would be the first Roller-compacted concrete (R.C.C) that will be implemented within 55 months.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.parhoon-tarh.com/newsdetail-25-en.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-08-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130201043130/http://www.parhoon-tarh.com/newsdetail-25-en.html |archivedate=2013-02-01 |df= }}</ref><ref>http://www.hydroworld.com/articles/2009/02/update---afghanistan-extends-bid-dates-to-build-pashdan-shah-wa-arus.html</ref> The dam will produce 1.2 Megawatts of power and irrigate 2700 hectares of land in addition to supplying drinking water for the residents of Kabul city. The project is an important scheme that will create jobs for 500 jobless Afghans during its completion process.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.designgroup.in/html/list_of_completed/pre_tender_services.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-08-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120723020156/http://www.designgroup.in/html/list_of_completed/pre_tender_services.htm |archivedate=2012-07-23 |df= }}</ref> The Project is located near the village of Nazim Khel on Shakardara River North West of [[Kabul Province]].
The Shah-wa-Arus Multipurpose Dam Project has the following major components:
*Roads, Bridges & other Infrastructure *Concrete Dam with Power Intake Structure *Power House *Pick up weir with Balancing Reservoir and Head Regulators<ref>{{cite web |url=http://parhoon-tarh.sampa.ir/proje100-proje101-proje112-en.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-08-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130218055549/http://parhoon-tarh.sampa.ir/proje100-proje101-proje112-en.html |archivedate=2013-02-18 |df= }}</ref>
